So the expanded #ChildTaxCredit:

-Reached more than 61 million children
-Cut monthly child poverty by 30%

I will not stop advocating for voting rights and saving the very foundation of our democracy. I was happy to join @AC360 last night to let everyone know why I’m not giving up. Check out some of our conversation here: https://t.co/UqBvw6KlQ6
In this moment, we are so blessed to have @POTUS and @VP in the White House. I am looking forward to year two of this Administration, and all we will do for Delaware and our country. (2/2)

As today marks one year since @POTUS and @VP were inaugurated, I have been reflecting on how far we have come. In this year, we've gotten shots in arms and money into people's pockets, created millions of jobs, and slashed child poverty among so much else. (1/2)

When it comes to voting rights, it's vitally important to remember that we are not just talking about policies. We're talking about our democracy, the foundation of this country. 

As Democrats, as Republicans, as Americans, this is really an issue for all of us.

🚨19 STATES 🚨 passed restrictive voting laws in 2021. We must recognize this moment for what it is: an emergency for our democracy.

The House has passed voting rights legislation and the Senate must do whatever is necessary to follow.
The Senate is currently debating the Freedom to Vote: John R. Lewis Act. This would be a good week for them to pass it.

Three years ago today, the Equal Rights Amendment became part of Delaware’s constitution. That was a proud and historic day in our state, and we should celebrate by recommitting to continuing our work until full equality under the law is realized by every Delawarean.
This is great news and I am excited that $225 million is going to Delaware! https://t.co/N2MRDvv0eI
Whether or not we protect voting rights isn’t a question of policy - it is the question of our democracy. And we have no time to waste. We must act now.
When the choice is between progress and process, we must always choose progress. https://t.co/3l1wBiHtTF
Voting rights are too important for us to let progress be stopped by process.
📣📣📣 https://t.co/4ctjk5yF9G

According to the @BrennanCenter, at least 19 states passed restrictive voting laws in 2021 — we must hear this warning and take action. We must do everything we can to get pro-voting legislation signed into law. https://t.co/4BwN7fXCwS

The expanded Child Tax Credit helped millions pay for necessities and stay or move out of poverty. In other words, it worked at a time when it was needed most. 

We cannot let this lifeline end as COVID cases rise around the country. https://t.co/mbM0jAUFnF

As of now, Americans with diabetes could pay up to $1,000/month out-of-pocket for life-saving insulin. It is simply unacceptable.

That is why I am so proud that the Build Back Better Act would cap the cost of insulin at $35.

The 13th Amendment was ratified today in 1865, ending the system of slavery that had existed in our country since its founding. The march towards racial justice still had a lot of ground to cover — and still does today — but we recognize this momentous day in our history.

Especially given how the pandemic has affected every facet of our lives, this opportunity to get health coverage to millions more Americans is a historic and life-changing one. We simply must pass this bill — it will save lives. https://t.co/vPqXEBz3J0

Here we go again: Republicans are asking #SCOTUS to overturn Roe v. Wade today. It's a direct threat to our reproductive rights and could strip abortion access from tens of millions.

Delaware has already codified Roe's protections and we must do the same federally.
I couldn’t agree more with these HBCU leaders, including our very own Dr. Tony Allen from @DelStateUniv. Let’s get this bill to @POTUS’ desk! https://t.co/SwuNVSxkX7
A very well-deserved honor. Congrats @KathyJenningsDE! https://t.co/chjWfCe8zH

Happy holidays everyone! https://t.co/7Z01aaqEGv

Today on this #TransDayOfRemembrance, I am keeping in my prayers each of the trans and gender non-conforming people whose lives were cut short this year. We must march on toward equal rights, and we can’t stop until every person can openly live their lives surrounded by love.
Proud doesn’t even begin to describe how I felt casting my vote in favor of the #BuildBackBetter Act on behalf of Delaware! https://t.co/snUoehYyVX

When @POTUS signs the bipartisan infrastructure bill into law, he will set in motion generational investments in:

🛣 Roads and bridges
✈️ Ports and airports
🚆 Public transportation
🔌 Broadband
🔋 Electric vehicles
🚰 Clean water

This is a big win for Delaware and our country!

Election Day 2022 is one year away.

In the last year, we’ve gotten shots into arms and money into people’s pockets. We’ve stood up for the rights of every American and made generational investments in our nation’s infrastructure. 

Now I can’t wait for what the next year brings!

One year ago today, we learned that @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris had won the @WhiteHouse! I am reflecting on how much we have accomplished since then, and am excited for all that we will do going forward. https://t.co/LbDA87W6Nd

I've already voted to codify Roe in the House, and I call on the Senate to do the same.

The #BuildBackBetter plan prioritizes everything from pre-school to elder care. Those long-overdue investments will create thousands of jobs and allow Americans all over the country to return to work, but simply, they’re just the right things to do.

Let's pass @POTUS' plan.

From extreme weather to sea level rise, the climate crisis poses many systemic threats to our economy.  The @WhiteHouse's #BuildBackBetter plan calls for crucial, substantial investments in our fight against the climate crisis — let's pass it. https://t.co/zUZFvZF3s5

🏡 #PaidLeaveForAll
💰 Extending the Child Tax Credit
🎓 Free 2-year community college
🩺 Expanding Medicare and Medicaid
📚 Universal pre-k

Let’s deliver for the American people!

We must make them permanent. https://t.co/gLT69oHl5g

Texas has effectively banned abortion at 6 weeks, before most even know they are pregnant. This is a dark day for everyone who supports access to safe, legal abortions.

This budget would transform countless lives across this country. From investments in families, to combatting the climate crisis, to creating millions of jobs, Democrats are here to meet the moment.

It would truly put us on the path to #BuildBackBetter. https://t.co/W6GVBSZIlB

“Do the math: when we add Sarah, Marie, and Eric, we multiply our chances for a better world.”

We must pass the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act the #ForThePeopleAct.

Today is #BlackWomensEqualPayDay.

Black women earn 63 cents for every dollar white men earn, and that means we must work 579 days to catch up to what white men are paid in 365 days. 

Simply put, it's past time for equal pay for equal work. https://t.co/fj9ad0RNDK
